messages.title: A BETTER PLAN FOR WORKING FAMILIES

keyPolicies.policyDescription: Labour's five pledges are: a strong economic foundation, higher living standards for working families, an NHS with the time to care, controls on immigration, and a country that works for the next generation better than the last.

issues.economy: A strong economic foundation without extra borrowing.
issues.health: An NHS with the time to care.
issues.socialWelfare: Higher living standards for working families.

quotes.text: None of Labour's commitments will require any extra borrowing.

images.caption: Labour leader Ed Miliband launches Labour's better plan for working families.

leaflet.additionalNotes: The leaflet mentions Nigel Farage's stance on the NHS, indicating competitive positioning on health services.
